                	<h2>MSW Handling</h2>
                	<p>Municipal solid waste from south Delhi and north Delhi in closed hook loaders or compactors are received at TOWMCL plant at the gate, where they are passed through Radioactive sensors, so that no unwanted waste or Radioactive waste enters the system. the loaders are rejected and concerned facility is informed in case of Radioactive material is detected. The loaders are weighed on an automatic weighing bridge, and they move to an inclined ramp, where they enter Truck Reception Hall.</p>
                	<p>Truck Reception Hall is where all the trucks with MSW are received and MSW is unloaded into the MSW Pit. This hall only has two openings IN and OUT for trucks and the hall is maintained under a negative pressure where air is not allowed to exit the hall. This air is further used in boilers for combustion.</p>
                	<h4>MSW Pits</h4>
                	<p>These are the pits inside the truck reception hall where all the MSW is unloaded and spraying of inoculum and spread of press mud is done while unloading of waste. The Floor of these Pits consists of proper Leachate collection system. MSW in the pits is homogenised time by time and stacked into a heap with the help of grab crane operated by operators in the control room so that leachate by effect of gravity and pressure comes down the waste rests into the pit for next 4 -5 days.</p>
