                        <h3>Waste to Energy</h3>
                        <p class="mb-50">Waste to energy (WtE), is the state-of-the art approach to the treatment of municipal solid waste. In addition to the energy recovery component that gives the process its name, it also includes the effective incineration of the waste, a powerful waste gas purification system, and the recovery of valuable materials from the residual materials. Waste to energy is an effective way to handle the waste by reducing its volume and recover the energy. It is a single approach towards two biggest problem of the world, waste management and depletion of fossils for energy production.</p>
                    </div>
